01:47:54,100 --> 01:47:58,059
<i>I spoke to Mørk's son the other day.</i>
<i>Christian.</i>

1277
01:47:59,773 --> 01:48:03,004
<i>- He's an American now.</i>
<i>- He lives in New York.</i>

1278
01:48:05,779 --> 01:48:09,237
<i>Max von Sydow should have played</i>
<i>Uncle Kessler.</i>

1279
01:48:09,449 --> 01:48:11,417
<i>You wanted him to play</i>
<i>the character.</i>

1280
01:48:12,285 --> 01:48:17,222
<i>But we avoided that</i>
<i>by offering him a low salary.</i>

1281
01:48:17,424 --> 01:48:19,790
<i>Then Ernst-Hugo got the part instead.</i>

1282
01:48:19,993 --> 01:48:26,125
<i>János Herskó. That was the man</i>
<i>from the film school in Stockholm.</i>

1283
01:48:26,833 --> 01:48:28,801
<i>They're all dead.</i>

1284
01:48:34,774 --> 01:48:37,800
<i>Yes, the eternal Jew.</i>

1285
01:48:38,011 --> 01:48:42,539
<i>Bo Christensen. He played the villain</i>
<i>in several Olsen Gang films.</i>

1286
01:48:43,250 --> 01:48:47,482
<i>He always wore</i>
<i>a white jacket and a hat.</i>

1287
01:48:49,489 --> 01:48:55,826
<i>Why</i>- 
<i>Why isn't he credited as "operator"?</i>

1288
01:48:56,029 --> 01:48:58,190
<i>In order to get</i>
<i>the money from France</i>

1289
01:48:58,298 --> 01:49:03,258
<i>Jean-Paul was listed</i>
<i>as a director of photography.</i>

1290
01:49:03,470 --> 01:49:08,772
<i>When they were upgraded</i>
<i>in the credits we got more money.</i>

1291
01:49:09,476 --> 01:49:13,936
<i>Henning Bendtsen has made</i>
<i>a beautiful black-and-white film.</i>

1292
01:49:14,147 --> 01:49:19,915
<i>His blood pressure suffered from it,</i>
<i>but he said it was my fault.</i>

1293
01:49:20,120 --> 01:49:24,022
<i>- He was probably right.</i>
<i>- Probably.</i>

1294
01:49:24,224 --> 01:49:27,682
<i>Philippe Bober.</i>
<i>- And Erik Crone.</i>

1295
01:49:27,894 --> 01:49:32,354
<i>Do you remember Philippe Guez?</i>
<i>The chubby French guy?</i>

1296
01:49:32,566 --> 01:49:34,534
<i>Yes.</i>

1297
01:49:35,368 --> 01:49:37,359
<i>Mital's right hand.</i>

1298
01:49:37,571 --> 01:49:40,165
<i>Who was the "Remember me" guy?</i>

1299
01:49:42,142 --> 01:49:47,842
<i>It was a producer I talked to</i> - 
<i>- He scared me to death.</i>

1300
01:49:49,149 --> 01:49:54,018
<i>Let's not bad-mouth him.</i>
<i>Maybe he sees this.</i>

1301
01:49:54,220 --> 01:49:57,348
<i>- He was a French</i> - 
<i>- I won't say his name here.</i>

1302
01:49:57,457 --> 01:50:02,053
<i>I just remember</i>
<i>he came up to me in Cannes:</i>

1303
01:50:02,262 --> 01:50:06,961
<i>"Remember me?"</i>
<i>- He almost had his Magnum ready.</i>

1304
01:50:07,167 --> 01:50:09,658
<i>He didn't need it.</i>
<i>He was so scary all by himself.</i>

1305
01:50:11,871 --> 01:50:16,001
<i>He's asked me to work with him since,</i>
<i>but I'm too scared to do it.</i>

1306
01:50:18,878 --> 01:50:23,474
<i>- Those French guys.</i>
<i>- They've got that Latin temper.</i>

1307
01:50:25,285 --> 01:50:27,651
<i>Can you read that?</i>
<i>- No.</i>

1308
01:50:27,754 --> 01:50:32,316
<i>Not even if I raise my head</i> - 

1309
01:50:38,765 --> 01:50:42,565
<i>I think the expenses ended</i>
<i>at about 27 million kroner.</i>

1310
01:50:42,769 --> 01:50:48,867
<i>That was a lot of money back then.</i>
<i>- How did we get all that money?</i>

1311
01:50:49,075 --> 01:50:53,944
<i>It was Sweden,</i>
<i>Germany and France</i> - 

1312
01:50:54,147 --> 01:50:56,115
<i>They've all gone bankrupt.</i>
<i>All our partners.</i>

1313
01:50:58,118 --> 01:51:03,055
<i>We tried to find</i>
<i>the German company recently.</i>

1314
01:51:03,256 --> 01:51:07,283
<i>- But it doesn't exist anymore.</i>
<i>- We've caused a lot of trouble.</i>

1315
01:51:09,929 --> 01:51:12,056
<i>And Nordisk Film was sold</i>
<i>to Egmont afterwards.</i>

1316
01:51:14,267 --> 01:51:15,598
<i>It was?</i>

1317
01:51:18,838 --> 01:51:22,797
<i>Panavision.</i>
<i>- Yes, it was important.</i>

1318
01:51:23,009 --> 01:51:26,740
<i>That it was Panavision. Back then,</i>
<i>some things were very important.</i>

1319
01:51:28,948 --> 01:51:31,314
<i>Things that didn't have</i>
<i>anything to do with profit.</i>

1320
01:51:33,520 --> 01:51:34,987
<i>"Mega."</i>

1321
01:51:35,188 --> 01:51:41,218
<i>Yes, Kjeld Wennick</i>
<i>did the soundtrack.</i>

1322
01:51:41,761 --> 01:51:47,563
<i>It hasn't been a hit on the charts.</i>

1323
01:51:47,767 --> 01:51:54,070
<i>But we'd hoped that it would be</i>
<i>a hit on the request programs.</i>

1324
01:51:54,874 --> 01:51:56,842
<i>"We would like to hear</i> Europa. <i>"</i>

1325
01:51:57,043 --> 01:52:00,774
<i>"We've collected some money</i>
<i>in a conductor's hat. "</i>

1326
01:52:03,283 --> 01:52:07,743
<i>Well, that was great.</i>
<i>I haven't seen it since, have you?</i>

1327
01:52:07,954 --> 01:52:14,917
<i>No. It wasn’t too bad.</i>
<i>But I'm really tired now.</i>

